	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 11:26 AM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>A good warrior is always aware of all casters status.&nbsp;&nbsp;One trick I like when working with one mob is to turn them around so that you can watch your casters.  Another trick is to assign "caster duty" to a second warrior/tank. Realize not all classes have taunt but regardless if casters are in trouble you need to do something.  What "caster duty" means is if a mob is on a caster one warrior stays on main mob and the second one (usually lower level one) goes after the mob.  After the mob is off the caster the idea is to return to the original mob.  It is always better to kill one mob first just to reduce numbers.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
